Skip the FSDP optimizer step on a non-finite OR explosively-large global grad_norm.

Applies AFTER 0001/0002/0003 (line numbers relative to the 0001-0003-patched
miles tree at UPSTREAM_PIN). The gpt-oss critic's eager bf16 backward
(attention sinks + q_proj) intermittently produces GARBAGE gradients on ~half
the batches — non-finite (NaN/inf) or explosively large (observed global
grad_norm 1e9-1e19, while healthy steps are ~0.2-4). clip_grad_norm_ cannot
help: a NaN makes the whole clip NaN, and a huge-finite norm gets rescaled to
1.0 and STEPPED, which slowly poisons the Adam moments until a permanent NaN
(first 100k critic run: NaN at step 592; norm-anchor rerun: NaN at step 87,
pred_norm perfectly stable the whole time -> the failure is the backward, not
the magnitude). Discard those batches entirely. grad_norm is the all-reduced
GLOBAL value, so every rank takes the same branch (no divergence); the loop-top
self.optimizer.zero_grad() of the next step clears the poisoned gradient.
Threshold from env NLA_GRAD_SKIP_THRESHOLD (default 1000; healthy grad_norm is
~4, step-0 transient ~118, explosions 1e4+). Healthy batches step normally.

--- a/miles/backends/fsdp_utils/actor.py
+++ b/miles/backends/fsdp_utils/actor.py
@@ -1,4 +1,5 @@
 import logging
+import math
 import os
 import random
 from argparse import Namespace
@@ -471,8 +489,24 @@ class FSDPTrainRayActor(TrainRayActor):
                 grad_norm = torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(self.model.parameters(), self.args.clip_grad)
                 grad_norm = grad_norm.full_tensor().item()

-                self.optimizer.step()
-                self.lr_scheduler.step()
+                # [NLA patch 0004] skip the optimizer step when the global
+                # grad_norm is non-finite OR explosively large. gpt-oss critic
+                # eager backward intermittently produces garbage gradients
+                # (norm 1e9-1e19 or NaN) on ~half the batches; norm-clip rescales
+                # the huge-finite ones to 1.0 and steps them, which poisons Adam
+                # over time -> permanent NaN. Discard those batches entirely
+                # (the next step zeroes grads at the loop top). grad_norm is the
+                # all-reduced global value, so all ranks take the same branch.
+                _grad_skip_thresh = float(os.environ.get("NLA_GRAD_SKIP_THRESHOLD", "1000.0"))
+                if math.isfinite(grad_norm) and grad_norm <= _grad_skip_thresh:
+                    self.optimizer.step()
+                    self.lr_scheduler.step()
+                else:
+                    logging.getLogger(__name__).warning(
+                        f"[NLA patch 0004] skip optimizer step rollout={rollout_id} "
+                        f"step={step_id}: grad_norm={grad_norm} (thresh={_grad_skip_thresh})"
+                    )

                 if self.args.ci_test:
